  = partial('signup', :locals => {:desc => "Decision<em>Flex</em> isn't out yet. Sign up to our newsletter and we'll let you know the second it's available."})

  %hr
  .row
    .col-md-12
      %h1.text-center
        What does Decision<em>Flex</em> look like in action?
  .row
    .col-md-6
      .thumbnail
        %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/hierarchy-shot.png", :alt => "Hierarchy of multiple decisions"}
        .caption
          %h3
            Hierarchy
          %p.lead
            The hierarchy lays out the decision, its actions, and the considerations for each action. It's easy to construct and read.
    .col-md-6
      .thumbnail
        %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/considerations-shot.png", :alt => "Animation curves weighing considerations"}
        .caption
          %h3
            Considerations
          %p.lead
            Tell Decision<em>Flex</em> how to weigh the factors influencing each action. Use animation curves to easily compare apples to oranges. No complex maths necessary.
    .col-md-6
      .thumbnail
        %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/docs-shot.png", :alt => "Fast and smooth"}
        .caption
          %h3
            Examples, tutorials and documentation
          %p.lead
            Comes with three wide-ranging example scenes, a tutorial and comprehensive documentation to get you up and running as fast as possible.
    .col-md-6
      .thumbnail
        %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/optimised-header.png", :alt => "Fast and smooth"}
        .caption
          %h3
            Optimised
          %p.lead
            Decision<em>Flex</em> runs fast with no allocations out of the box. It copes with pooling. It has tools to timeslice decisions for predictiability and budgeting. 
      
